<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 3:22PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Richland, Ashland and northwestern Wayne Counties through 415 PM
EDT...
At 322 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Savannah, or 8 miles northwest of Ashland, moving southeast at 25
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ashland, West Salem, Hayesville, Savannah, Polk, Sullivan,
Jeromesville, Bailey Lakes, Congress, Rowsburg, Nova, Mohicanville,
Nankin, Reedsburg, Shenandoah and Olivesburg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
